# Code Placement

## Overview

| Tipo | Local | Exemplo |
|------|-------|---------|
| Parsers | `lib/parsers.ts` ou `lib/{domain}-parsers.ts` | `parsePhone`, `parseDate` |
| Formatters | `lib/formatters.ts` | `formatDate`, `formatPhone` |
| Supabase queries | `modules/{domain}/` | `get-patients-by-user-phone.ts` |
| Modules (business logic) | `modules/{domain}/` | `patients/`, `cases/`, `authenticated-users/` |
| UI primitives (Shadcn) | `components/ui/` | `Button`, `Input`, `Card` |
| Feature components | `components/` ou `app/.../components/` | `PatientForm`, `CaseList` |
| Theme / styles | `app/globals.css`, `tailwind.config.ts` | CSS variables, tokens |

---

## lib/

Pure utilities, no React, no I/O (except shared constants/env).

```
lib/
├── parsers.ts        # parsePhone, parseDate, parsePayload (Zod schemas)
├── formatters.ts     # formatDate, formatPhone, formatCrm
├── constants.ts      # Product constants
├── env.ts            # Env validation (Zod)
├── errors.ts         # Custom error classes
├── get-authenticated-user-phone.ts # Auth resolution (uses Supabase)
├── supabase/         # Supabase client setup (client.ts, server.ts, middleware.ts)
└── utils.ts          # cn(), other misc helpers (if needed)
```

- **Parsers**: transform string/unknown → typed value; use Zod for validation.
- **Formatters**: typed value → display string; pure, no I/O.

---

## modules/

Business logic + Supabase queries. One domain per folder; one export per file.

```
modules/
├── supabase/
│   └── queries/      # Auth: sign-in-with-password.ts, exchange-code-for-session.ts
├── patients/         # get-patients-by-user-phone.ts, create-patient.ts, etc.
├── cases/
├── case-messages/
├── authenticated-users/
└── report-templates/
```

- Each file: one main function (e.g. `getPatientsByUserPhone(supabase, userPhone)`).
- Supabase client is always the first argument.
- **Nunca** chamar Supabase diretamente em componentes; usar módulos em `modules/`.
- Types can be colocated in `types.ts` inside the module or in a shared `types/` if used across modules.

---

## components/

### components/ui/

Shadcn UI primitives only (Radix-based). Do not add business logic here.

- `Button`, `Input`, `Label`, `Card`, `Dialog`, `Select`, `Table`, etc.
- **Obrigatório:** usar componentes de `components/ui/` em páginas e forms; nunca criar `<input>`, `<button>`, `<label>` manualmente.
- Composable, generic, styled via Tailwind + CSS variables.
- Ver regras: `ux-ui-minimalist`, `design-system`, `radix`.

### components/ or app/.../components/

Feature-specific components that use `components/ui` and modules.

```
components/
├── ui/               # Shadcn primitives
├── dashboard/        # Sidebar, Header, PatientForm, CaseList
└── forms/            # Shared forms (PatientForm, etc.) – opcional
```

- Prefer `components/` for reusable pieces; `app/(dashboard)/pacientes/components/` for page-specific.
- Use `"use client"` only when needed (hooks, events, browser APIs).

---

## Theme (Shadcn + Tailwind)

- **Tailwind config**: `tailwind.config.ts` – theme colors, fonts.
- **CSS variables**: `app/globals.css` – Shadcn theming (`--background`, `--foreground`, etc.).
- **No separate theme folder** unless you have multiple themes or complex token systems.

```
app/globals.css       # :root { --background, --foreground, ... }
tailwind.config.ts   # theme.extend.colors, etc.
```
